cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.ET 

The paper discusses a real-time control system for EUV lithography, which involves image processing and computational modeling. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.AR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CV (Computer Graphics and Computer-Aided Design) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes the use of GPUs to accelerate the computations, which falls under the cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of compression and mixed-precision arithmetic, which is related to the cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) sub-category.
